	(79, 'Ahmad Nizam Bin Adnan', '(+60)1131909578', '00000037236@student.imu.edu.my', 'IMU Bukit Jalil', 'Friends/Family', 'Health Fair', 'It is a community event that provides free health screening services and educates the public on health-related topics.', '2024-05-04', '2024-05-04', 'Pavilion Bukit Jalil, Level 5, Function Room', '350', 'For Use at Exhibitor Stalls', 'No', 'IMU Health Fair is a student-led event that involves a select group of IMU\'s healthcare professionals and lecturers. This fair entails health screening programs that will be made free for any visitor and will be supervised by respective professionals. Consultation booths will be set up also for further professional advice. \r\n\r\nThis Health Fair is designed to enhance community health and well-being through the implementation of a comprehensive health screening program. The project aims to proactively identify and address health risks, promote the early detection of potential medical conditions, and empower individuals to adopt healthier lifestyles. By fostering a culture of preventive care, the project strives to contribute to the overall improvement of community health outcomes.\r\n\r\nThe Health Fair offers the public a unique opportunity to prioritize their well-being through a comprehensive health screening program. By proactively identifying and addressing health risks, the project facilitates the early detection of potential medical conditions, empowering individuals to embrace healthier lifestyles. This preventive care approach not only enhances individual health but collectively contributes to the overall improvement of community well-being.\r\n\r\nThe Health Fair serves as a strategic collaboration with IMU Healthcare Clinic, extending the reach of preventive care initiatives. By actively involving the clinic in the health screening program, participants can collect their blood test reports at the IMU clinic, enhancing the clinic\'s visibility and promoting its services. The partnership not only fosters a culture of health within the community but also positions the clinic as a vital resource for proactive health management. This collaboration strengthens the clinic\'s role as a community-focused healthcare provider, contributing to improved community health outcomes and fostering lasting connections with the public.\r\n\r\nDuring the event, health screening booths will be available for visitors, including medical, dental, chiropractic, traditional chinese medicine and even psychology booths. Educational booths will also be set up for people of all ages, also catering to children and the elderly.', '[]', '0', '0', NULL, '0', '17', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Approved', 'NotFilled', NULL, '14ctn 500ml', NULL, 'Naomis', '[""]', NULL, '2024-01-29 19:24:07', '2024-02-04 23:24:57', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'none', NULL, NULL),
