	(106, 'Chang Rui Wei', '011-10809562', 'unmc.chineseorchestra@gmail.com', 'University of Nottingham Malaysia Chinese Orchestra', 'I’m Jantzen User', 'University of Nottingham Malaysia Chinese Orchestra “Ethereal Blossoms” Concert', 'Chinese Orchestra Concert', '2024-03-23', '2024-03-23', 'The Temple of Fine Arts Kuala Lumpur, 116, Jalan Berhala, Brickfields, 50470 Kuala Lumpur, Wilayah Persekutuan Kuala Lumpur', 'Approximately 300 people', 'For Team/Crew Utilization', 'Yes', 'Since the founding of our society, University of Nottingham Malaysia Chinese Orchestra (UNMCO) has shown commitment and dedication in promoting the beauty of Chinese Orchestral Music to all. In the past few years, we have organised multiple Chinese Orchestra Concerts that have always been well received. Our upcoming event, UNM CO Concert: “Ethereal Blossoms” on 23rd March 2024 (Saturday) will be held physically at The Temple of Fine Arts Kuala Lumpur Malaysia, with targeted participants from our university students and also open to the public. ‘Ethereal’ means the music portrayed as transporting the audience to a dreamlike realm, creating an atmosphere that feels almost intangible or beyond the physical world. ‘Blossoms’ evoke the image of flowers blooming, representing the richness and beauty of the music. It is also related to one of the songs performed in the concert. ‘Ethereal Blossoms’ represents the concert where the music played is not only melodically beautiful but also carries a sense of transient and exquisite nature of life. This event will be conducted bilingually to allow people of all backgrounds to enjoy the show together with approximately 300 audiences expected to participate in this event.', '[]', '0', '0', NULL, '0', '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Processing', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2024-02-04 17:48:33', '2024-02-04 23:19:30', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2024-02-04