	(113, 'ZOE LEE LING HUI', '018-7639123', 'zoelh2301@gmail.com', 'SMMAMS (SCOME)', 'Events', 'First Aid Workshop: "Your Quick Response, Their Second Chance"', 'First Aid Workshop', '2024-03-09', '2024-03-09', 'SRI KDU Schools (Hall) Address: 3, 5, 7, Jalan Teknologi 2/1, Taman Sains Selangor, Kota Damansara, 47810 Petaling Jaya, Selangor', '200', 'Complimentary items for attendees (e.g., in gift bags or as souvenirs)', 'No', 'Dear Jantzen Water (Mineral Water & Water Delivery) - HQ Puchong Branch,\r\n \r\nI hope this email finds you well. My name is Zoe Lee Ling Hui, and I am reaching out to you on behalf of the executing committee of a first aid workshop, titled "Your Quick Response, Their Second Chance", organized under the esteemed societies of the Malaysian Medical Association (MMA) – the Society of MMA Medical Students (SMMAMS) and the Standing Committee on Medical Education (SCOME). We are excited to inform you about an upcoming event that we believe aligns perfectly with your commitment to community welfare and safety.\r\n \r\nThe Malaysian Medical Association (MMA) serves as a leading professional organization for physicians in Malaysia, working to advance healthcare standards and advocate for the interests of the medical community. Within the MMA, the Society of MMA Medical Students (SMMAMS) is a group of enthusiastic medical students committed to professional development, networking, and community engagement. Additionally, the Standing Committee on Medical Education (SCOME), operating under the MMA, focuses on improving medical education standards and fostering collaboration between students and professionals. By collaborating with these esteemed organizations, our First Aid Workshop not only emphasizes community safety but also integrates the expertise and passion of medical students and professionals to make a lasting impact on healthcare and education in Malaysia.\r\n \r\nEvent Details: \r\nDate: 9th March 2024\r\nTime: 8:30 am - 5 pm\r\nVenue: Sri KDU 