	(137, 'Sashvini Sivarathanam', '601139019403', 'introbudukm.sponsorship@gmail.com', 'PERSIAP UKM', 'Events', 'INTROBUD 2023/2024 PERSIAP UKM', 'Educational', '2024-04-19', '2024-04-19', 'Faculty of Medicine, UKM, Jalan Yaacob Latif, Bandar Tun Razak, 56000 Cheras, Wilayah Persekutuan Kuala Lumpur', '400', 'Complimentary items for attendees (e.g., in gift bags or as souvenirs)', 'Yes', 'Introduction and Interaction Day, also known as INTROBUD 2023/2024, is a programme conducted by the Medical Students’ Association (PERSIAP) of the Faculty of Medicine, National University of Malaysia (UKM) to welcome our first-year students. This event is held annually with its ultimate aim of allowing exposure to the life and challenges in the medical field through speeches by experienced professors and interactively through games and sharing sessions. It also serves to introduce and establish a good rapport between the juniors and their buddies (buddy) who act as student mentors to guide them throughout the 5 years of medical course through a system titled the buddy system.', '["uploads/Sponsorship Letter INTROBUD 2023 OFFICIAL.docx-2.pdf1707904662.pdf"]', '0', '0', NULL, '0', '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Approved', 'NotFilled', NULL, 'check on water qty & sponsor in return', NULL, 'Naomis', '[""]', NULL, '2024-02-14 01:57:46', '2024-02-15 17:02:22', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'none', NULL, NULL),
	(138, 'Sarah Padzil', '01125873006', 'srikandi.simposium@gmail.com', 'Persatuan Srikandi Kebangsaan UKM, Universiti Kebangsaan Malaysia', 'I’m Jantzen User', 'Simposium Srikandi 2024', 'Community & Educational', '2024-05-11', '2024-05-15', 'Panggung Seni dan Dewan Canselor Tun Abdul Razak (DECTAR), UKM', '128 invited female students from 32 higher education institutes  and open to the public', 'Complimentary items for attendees (e.g., in gift bags or as souvenirs)', 'Yes', 'Simposium Srikandi 2024 is a programme that consists of three main components which are\r\npresentations, exhibitions, and sales. All of these components are designed to serve as a platform to amplify the voices and roles of women in this globalization era. The paperwork presentation session will be participated by 128 invited female students from 32 higher education institutes. Meanwhile, the exhibition session will involve 50 government and non-government organizations to provide exposure on women, careers, education, family, and legislation. Finally, the sales session that includes nearly 92 sellers, aims to promote businesses owned by women entrepreneurs and at the same time inspiring other women to venture into the business field.', '["uploads/2. Executive Summary.pdf1707962436.pdf", "uploads/1. Official Letter (SS2024_016).pdf1707962436.pdf", "uploads/5. Authority.pdf1707962436.pdf", "uploads/4. Programme Approval.pdf1707962436.pdf", "uploads/6. Tax Exemption.pdf1707962436.pdf", "uploads/3. Infographic.pdf1707962436.pdf"]', '0', '80', NULL, '0', '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Approved', 'NotFilled', NULL, 'check on the water qty as they req a lot. \r\nsponsor in returns too', NULL, 'Naomis', '[""]', NULL, '2024-02-14 18:00:43', '2024-02-15 17:01:57', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'none', NULL, NULL),
	(139, 'Anis Najihah Abd Razak', '(+60) 016-9452146', 'anis_21001434@utp.edu.my', 'Chembusters of Universiti Teknologi PETRONAS (UTP)', 'I’m Jantzen User', 'Chembusters Community Engagement Project', 'Educational, Community, International', '2024-04-20', '2024-05-03', 'ogyakarta, Indonesia (Universitas Islam Indonesia)Kaliurang St No.Km. 14,5, Krawitan, Umbulmartani, Ngemplak, Sleman Regency, Special Region of Yogyakarta 55584, Indonesia', '200', 'For Team/Crew Utilization', 'No', 'With the aim of producing a community engagement project for social improvement, showcasing leadership, and teamwork skills, HEB 1012 Community Engagement Project (CEP) is an obligatory course needed to be taken by all Universiti Teknologi PETRONAS (UTP) undergraduate students. This subject is authorized as a national requirement by the Ministry of Education in the context of MPU (Mata Pelajaran Umum/General Studies). Chembusters Community Enggagement project is planned to bring forth a platform for students to regulate and experience an internationally based community outreach project to shape the participants, especially the UTP students into remarkable individuals with exceptional skills. Additionally, it fulfils the UTP’s vision of increasing the number of students\' international experience during their education at Universiti Teknologi PETRONAS (UTP). Brimming with passion, Chembusters wishes to tackle the issue of the declining interest of the youth in the industrial sector concentrated along the pillar of education focusing on Pure Science and Technology. Exposing the participants to a Pure Science and Technology-themed journey filled with interactive and informative activities is a great strategy for inspiring the students while providing them with a one-in-a-million opportunity to explore the glorious Pure Science and Technology sector. In addition, throughout the fortnight program, students will be able to cohesively interact with the Universitas Islam Indonesia (UII) students, unlocking the different perspectives and creative ideas from both sides that will help in coping with this problem and promoting deep understanding and mutual respect. Other than that, several activities such as educational talk, Pure Science and Technology explore-race, to strengthen the bond of the students of UTP and UII students which will unconsciously create a large networking circle, filled with individuals with the same objectives and ideas, moving toward one dream of generating betterment in the society and throughout the world.', '["uploads/UII PROPOSAL.pdf1707976730.pdf", "uploads/Sponsorship Proposal Chembusters .pdf1707976730.pdf"]', '0', '0', NULL, '0', '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Approved', 'NotFilled', NULL, 'check on water qty & sponsor in return', NULL, 'Naomis', '[""]', NULL, '2024-02-14 21:58:54', '2024-02-15 17:01:13', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'none', NULL, NULL),
	(140, 'Muhammad Amirul Bin Nasrul Edie', '(+60) 1119199405', 'mirulkut@gmail.com', 'Persatuan Mahasiswa Selangor Universiti Malaya', 'Social Media', 'Iftar Perdana Persatuan Mahasiswa Selangor Universiti Malaya', 'Community', '2024-03-30', '2024-03-30', 'Kompleks Perdanasiswa Universiti Malaya,50603 Wilayah Persekutuan Kuala Lumpur', '400', 'Complimentary items for attendees (e.g., in gift bags or as souvenirs)', NULL, 'We from Persatuan Mahasiswa Selangor (PERMAS) Universiti Malaya will be conducting an event during ramadhan called Iftar Perdana PERMAS.The inaugural iftar for PERMAS aims to foster gratitude and unity among Selangor students. Additionally, it seeks to strengthen relationships and expand networks among them. The event also aims to share blessings with Selangor B40 students at the University of Malaya. It involves 400 participants, including Muslim and non-Muslim students, and runs from 5:30 PM to 9:00 PM on 30 of March 2024.The event will be conducted by The Welfare and Unity Exco Of PERMAS and it will take place at Kompleks Perdanasiswa Universiti Malaya.The Welfare and Unity Exco organizes it to instill gratitude and awareness while promoting friendly relations through various activities. Importantly, it serves as a platform to gather Selangor students both on and off-campus. We wholeheartedly hope for support to realize this event. We are truly delightful if your company can consider to give sponsorship for this event.It would be really helpful for us to share the kindness to all students in Universiti Malaya. We are aware that your company has sponsored most of the event conducted here in Universiti Malaya.Hence,we are looking forward to continue distributing and exposing your brand to others. We believe that partnering with Jantzen for this event would not only benefit our organization and attendees but also demonstrate your dedication to supporting the academic and social development of students in Selangor. Thank you for considering our proposal. We look forward to the possibility of working together to make the inaugural iftar event a success.', '["uploads/KKP IFTAR PERDANA PERMAS.pdf1707983930.pdf", "uploads/Surat kelulusan Iftar Perdana Permas.pdf1707983930.pdf", "uploads/Kertas kerja tajaan iftar perdana PERMAS.pdf1707983930.pdf"]', '0', '17', NULL, '0', '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Approved', 'NotFilled', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Naomis', '[""]', NULL, '2024-02-14 23:58:53', '2024-02-15 17:00:27', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'none', NULL, NULL);
